Ease of Agent Creation
What is the process for creating and deploying a new agent?

Does it involve a graphical interface, command-line tools, or coding?
How quickly can an agent be built and made operational?

Are there tools or automations to simplify this process?
Can agents be created by non-developers or less technical team members?

Is there support for low-code or no-code creation?
Does the solution support cloning existing agents for modification?

How flexible is it for adapting agents to new use cases?


  Template Standardization
Does the solution follow a standardized templating system for defining workflows and agent logic?

What format does it use (e.g., YAML, JSON, or code-based)?
Are there pre-built templates available?

Can these templates be extended or customized for specific use cases?
How consistent are the templates across different agents and use cases?

Are there mechanisms to ensure adherence to best practices?
Are templates modular?

Can components of one template (e.g., workflows, connectors) be reused in another?


  Utilization of Connectors
How does the solution handle connectors?

Are connectors modular and reusable?
What types of connectors are supported?

Are there pre-existing connectors for databases, APIs, messaging systems, and other common platforms?
What is the process for linking connectors to agents?

Is this automatic, or does it require manual setup?
What happens if a connector fails or becomes unavailable?

Are there fallback or retry mechanisms?
Can connectors be orchestrated for complex workflows?

For example, can data flow from one connector trigger actions in another?


  Support for Multiple LLMs
Does the platform support multiple LLM providers like OpenAI, Bedrock, and Google Gemini?

Are these integrations native, or do they require custom configurations?
Can developers select and configure the LLM model as part of the agent's setup?

Is the choice of model passed as a parameter or configuration?
Is the platform flexible enough to support future LLMs or proprietary models?

How easy is it to add support for new models?
Ease of Configuration
How do developers specify the LLM for an agent?

Is it done through a configuration file, template, or UI?
Can different agents use different LLMs within the same system?

Does the platform allow for simultaneous usage of multiple LLM APIs?
Are there abstractions or APIs that simplify switching between LLMs?

Can developers try different LLMs without modifying the core agent logic?


  Knowledge Sync and Vector Database Integration
Does the platform support integration with vector databases?

Which vector databases are supported (e.g., Pinecone, Weaviate, Chroma, Milvus)?
Can it connect to multiple vector DBs simultaneously?
How do agents interact with vector databases for knowledge retrieval?

Is there built-in support for querying vector DBs for relevant embeddings?
Does the platform provide abstractions to simplify RAG-based workflows?
Can agents dynamically update or sync knowledge to the vector database?

How is newly acquired knowledge stored and indexed for future use?
Are there tools for managing and visualizing vector database contents?

Can developers or admins inspect embeddings, indexes, and search results?
